BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Book Club - Hope in the Dark
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T200000
UID:53b10e734b1ffd1ee171702cbe1b87bf@coolpetaluma.org
DESCRIPTION:Cool Petaluma Book Club Our book for April\, Hope in the Dark 
 by Rebecca Solnit\, shows us why we should not give up hope\, even though 
 our future is uncertain. In fact\, we should be committed to it in all its
  unknowability. PLEASE NOTE: There are 5 copies at Copperfield’s\; ask f
 or one at the counter. Let them know you’re with the Cool Petaluma Clima
 te Book Club. Plus\, get 10% off! #block-48fda9e02d14584b80b1 { --tweak-te
 xt-block-radius: 0px 0px 0px 0px\; --tweak-text-block-radius: unset\; --st
 roke-style: none\;--stroke-thickness: 6px\; border-width: unset\; border-s
 tyle: unset\; border-color: unset\; background-color: unset\;}#block-48fda
 9e02d14584b80b1 .sqs-html-content { --tweak-text-block-padding: 6% 6% 6% 6
 %\; padding: unset\;}#block-48fda9e02d14584b80b1 { mix-blend-mode: var(--t
 weak-text-block-blend )\; } #block-48fda9e02d14584b80b1 { } RSVP Here #blo
 ck-41ef93226c8a0444c843 {--sqs-block-content-flex: 0\; } Hope in the Dark 
 Solnit’s book is a manifesto for hope in place of the despair that engul
 fs many activists when their campaigns to make the world a better place or
  safeguard local values from globalized corporations do not bear immediate
  fruit. Solnit advocates for embracing the darkness of an uncertain future
  and campaigning from the perspective that previously unforeseen changes a
 re always possible. In this book\, she seeks to safeguard against the cult
 ural amnesia in which people forget that previously unthinkable events cha
 nged history\, such as obtaining suffrage for women after millennia of pat
 riarchy. In addition\, she emphasizes that no easy cause-and-effect relati
 onship exists between activism and seeing changes realized. Instead\, the 
 path to change twists and turns\, with many defeats as well as small victo
 ries. #block-5ce66d8084f2469abf99 { --tweak-text-block-radius: 0px 0px 0px
  0px\; --tweak-text-block-radius: unset\; --stroke-style: none\;--stroke-t
 hickness: 6px\; border-width: unset\; border-style: unset\; border-color: 
 unset\; background-color: unset\;}#block-5ce66d8084f2469abf99 .sqs-html-co
 ntent { --tweak-text-block-padding: 6% 6% 6% 6%\; padding: unset\;}#block-
 5ce66d8084f2469abf99 { mix-blend-mode: var(--tweak-text-block-blend )\; } 
 #block-5ce66d8084f2469abf99 { } &nbsp\; [ { "id": "04388466-7135-4ccc-9916
 -e993de72b63e" } ] Get your copy &amp\; start reading: Petaluma Library Go
 odReads Copperfield’s Books - Tell them you are with the Cool Petaluma B
 ook Club for 10% discount! #block-3fc3e09189c20756044f { --tweak-text-bloc
 k-radius: 0px 0px 0px 0px\; border-radius: var(--tweak-text-block-radius)\
